; v6.test
;
; An IPv6-first zone. Only the two NS hosts and the apex
; have A records; everything else is AAAA-only. Useful
; for showing what a happy-eyeballs client does when AAAA
; resolves but A does not, and for seeing the wire shape
; of an IPv6 address in RDATA (16 raw bytes vs 4 for A).
;
; Try in the demo: query www.v6.test for AAAA (works),
; then for A (NODATA -- name exists but not at type A,
; response shows zero answers and an SOA in authority).
; Compare the bytes: AAAA RDATA is 16 bytes long, A
; RDATA is 4.
;
$ORIGIN v6.test.
$TTL 3600
@               IN  SOA   ns1.v6.test. admin.v6.test. (
                          2026010101 3600 1800 604800 86400 )
@               IN  NS    ns1.v6.test.
@               IN  NS    ns2.v6.test.
@               IN  A     198.51.100.1
@               IN  AAAA  2001:db8:6::1
ns1             IN  A     198.51.100.2
ns1             IN  AAAA  2001:db8:6::2
ns2             IN  A     198.51.100.3
ns2             IN  AAAA  2001:db8:6::3
www             IN  AAAA  2001:db8:6::80
api             IN  AAAA  2001:db8:6::a91
api             IN  AAAA  2001:db8:6::a92
api             IN  AAAA  2001:db8:6::a93
cdn             IN  AAAA  2001:db8:6::cd0
mail            IN  AAAA  2001:db8:6::ed1
ipv6-only       IN  AAAA  2001:db8:6::fff
